how many people on here have an agent how do u get one most people who have a legit agent aren't going to give you that info at least not on here if they're with some scam agent that they paid to get they'll probably advertise it if you want to find a legitimate agent to represent you for commercials tv film go to sag org use the dropdown menu on the right labeled 'resources' and choose 'agent information' on the next screen on the left choose 'find a sag franchised agent' and follow the directions you can look up agents all over the us but there are higher concentrations where the work is los angeles ny il fl ga etc another great resource is ross reports especially because they update their info so often but not all of the agents they list are sag and you have to pay for the list that doesn t mean they re not legit but that s why i always tell people to start with the sag list it s free and those agents have signed an agreement to put the actor first www rossreports com if you subscribe to backstage com you can get a combo subscription which can come in handy but can also get quite expensive then you can send the agencies your headshot resume and a cover letter stating that you are seeking representation and wait to see if they call you in for an interview you never call the agencies directly that is a big no no at least it is in la please remember that reputable agents take exactly of your pay after they help you get a job not one cent more and not one cent before anything else is a scam this is strictly for talent agents not modeling agents or talent managers who take different percentages once you have an agent they will get you the auditions but until then you can check out actorsaccess com you can also see if your state has a film alliance commission society or whatever your state calls theirs some have more than one sometimes they post audition information for projects filming locally for theatre and other auditions on backstage you can go to backstage com or www actorsequity com click on casting call if you find the audition on the equity site you still may be able to go as long as their not taking appointments from equity actor's only on backstage com you have to pay to get all of the info but the initial search is free and you may be able to see enough info to find out the rest on your own without paying good luck Modelling agency Internet fraud Spam (electronic) Open access Advance fee fraud Online Copyright Infringement Liability Limitation Act MMORPG Professional wrestling slang E-mail spam Advertising Unemployment Cable television Search engine optimization Poker jargon Teletext Mail fraud United States Postal Service National Football League Plame affair MapleStory Security (finance) AmigaOS World Wide Web Web traffic Slot machine Oakland Athletics Mattress Corporate governance RuneScape cheats Voice actor Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Divorce Database management system Mail-order bride Enterprise content management Principal-agent problem The Standard Google Windows XP Yellow Pages Microsoft RuneScape Bond 2005 Kashmir earthquake Pyramid scheme North American Numbering Plan Make money fast HTML element Gmail Virgin Mobile Digital rights management Child support Kazaa Monopoly (game) Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Political campaign American Football League Webcomic Stock Channel 4 Microeconomics Open Directory Project X Window System Government of France Podcasting Financial audit Biodiesel Airline Confidence trick Spyware Washington gubernatorial election, 2004 America Online Salary cap ITunes E-mail Neopets Notary public Oxford English Dictionary Legal research Free trade Church of Scientology Economics 2004 U.S. presidential election controversy, vote suppression Jeff Gannon Annuity Wal-Mart Appeal Charles Ponzi Call centre The Price Is Right Domain name Telephone numbering plan 